According to La Gazzetta dello Sport, Milan midfielder Franck Kessié will likely snub a free transfer to Tottenham Hotspur in the summer as he prefers to stay in Serie A and both Inter and Juventus are interested.  Kessié has snubbed Milan’s contract offer worth €6.5m-a-year and is determined to leave the Rossoneri as a free agent at the end of the season. According to La Gazzetta dello Sport, Inter have already sounded out the midfielder’s availability, but the Nerazzurri will face competition from Juventus.   Everton set to announce new manager     Liverpool set to beat Tottenham to £37.5m Luis Diaz…     GAMBIA VS CAMEROON: Underdog faces topdogs in AFCON testy…   Read Also: Everton set to announce new manager Tottenham Hotspur have also met the player’s agent, but Kessié seems willing to stay in Serie A. The meeting with Spurs is described as ‘not positive’ as the Ivory Coast international prefers Serie A stay. Inter signed Hakan Calhanoglu as a free agent from Milan last summer and hope Kessié will follow his former teammate’s path.